d12720","position":{"commit_sha":"308c5d9890cbccb56c991bde79de823238d41681","position":"1784694924049100001-33ee6bd2-f3a8-411d-b710-e6205fd12720"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Operator-attested live-store recovery: under rebar._store.lock.write_lock at expected pre-cleanup tickets HEAD ef632f720c46d6754d6874252ac0a90bc503e226, moved exact namespaces 3601-11b8-430a-4639, 6c56-d5e4-2443-4cf8, 7b3a-26ca-c6ae-47e1, T-1, and rec-0000 to recoverable quarantine /private/tmp/rebar-jira-reb-1160/.scratch/d540-live-store-quarantine/pre-cleanup-ef632f720. SHA256.json records every file hash. Committed 32 tracked synthetic sidecar deletions on tickets as 26fd3b26b567a2f18a23046ed19387adca4dab1e and pushed origin/tickets; empty UUID dirs were also removed. Post-cleanup tracker is clean and all five namespaces are absent.","timestamp":1784689742179985001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Verification evidence: focused held-out oracle 45 passed; defect-seeded removal of completion_sidecar.emit isolation made the ambient-store HEAD assertion fail, then restoration returned green. make check passed. Full default live-corpus suite passed: 6856 passed, 59 skipped, 13 warnings in 1769.01s. Shared tracker moved during that 29m window only through attributable real reconciler/review/ticket commits; none of the synthetic namespaces reappeared during that run. A later pre-fix checkout emitted one rec-0000 PASS at d83325374; direct replay of the patched node left live tracker HEAD ce4405a3f unchanged, proving this worktree's isolation. That one event was quarantined with SHA256 e5dc11c4... and removed under the canonical lock in tickets commit 9f43cc16118b880ccbeca8e24cbc9a236c9814ba. Five-axis review: APPROVE; test-only change, production emission unchanged, no dependencies/security/performance impact.","timestamp":1784694445760257001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Gerrit #879 patchset 1 CI exposed collateral .pytest_cache creation by nested pytest in clean runners. Fixed the oracle helper to pass -p no:cacheprovider, preserving the nested behavioral run while preventing checkout mutation. Focused 45 passed and make check passed after correction; amended commit cc255012cdaacc054598eab8852c8d1bcfea75dd pushed as patchset 2 with the same Change-Id.","timestamp":1784694924049100001}],"created_at":1784689134593021001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"cf15d19f-3253-41f2-a8bc-d5e1a0b9af23","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"acaf-bb4d-9eba-470c"}],"description":"## Problem\nThe default test suite writes synthetic plan-review/completion sidecars under T-1 and rec-0000 in the checkout live .tickets-tracker and leaves empty UUID ticket directories. These namespaces have no CREATE event, so the new one-pass PlanRelationSnapshot preload fails every real review with reducer-error before the LLM. Existing tracked synthetic events and empty directories require explicit recovery; strict snapshot failure must remain fail-closed for genuinely corrupt real ticket material.\n\n## Plan\n- Identify the exact tests/production boundary that resolves an omitted repo_root to the live checkout and reproduce each leak deterministically.\n- Add RED isolation coverage proving synthetic gate/verifier tests cannot change the live tracker HEAD or create directories there; use explicit temporary repositories or mocked event writers at the responsible test boundaries.\n- Preserve production event emission semantics; fix only test fixture isolation unless evidence identifies a production API bug.\n- Recover empty directories and tracked synthetic T-1/rec-0000 namespaces with a history-preserving tickets-branch commit and a recoverable quarantine, recording exact evidence.\n- Re-run focused tests, make check, the default suite, and review-plan 75de to prove the live store remains clean and the real review reaches its LLM gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Focused tests identify and reproduce every live-store writer responsible for T-1 and rec-0000 sidecars.\n- [ ] Synthetic plan-review and completion-verifier tests use explicit isolated stores or mocked event writers and do not mutate the checkout tracker.\n- [ ] The full default suite leaves the checkout tracker HEAD and directory set unchanged.\n- [ ] Production plan-review/completion sidecar emission remains covered and unchanged.\n- [ ] Strict relation snapshots still reject genuine reducer corruption; no fail-open skip is added.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Empty synthetic directories and tracked T-1/rec-0000 events are removed from the live tree through recoverable, history-preserving cleanup.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] review-plan 75de reaches the LLM gate after cleanup instead of returning reducer-error.\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"d4dc7203-ec92-4d8c-9ffc-7b91766ba9d8","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["test-isolation","plan-review","ticket-store"],"ticket_id":"d540-fdd1-318f-49a5","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Test verifier sidecars pollute the live ticket store","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["4fc7c280-4de5-4d91-a8dd-8eb0e4f1ae56","cf15d19f-3253-41f2-a8bc-d5e1a0b9af23","d4dc7203-ec92-4d8c-9ffc-7b91766ba9d8","e6795e8a-68f7-48c3-a6c5-fac9a086863c","e657328f-8da0-4911-9cfa-377169d9f500","25a65da5-7576-405f-b7d5-eb3ccc7f6988","33ee6bd2-f3a8-411d-b710-e6205fd12720"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784694924049100002,"uuid":"565312f0-7149-40cf-bfb9-eeb63a3eeda2"}